docs: compact README with logo and collapsible sections

Five-point visual rework addressing "reads like an unstyled long
document" feedback:

1. Hero swapped from plain h1 to SVG logo + wordmark.
   Routing-tree mark: root with medical cross branching to three
   child nodes - concentric (existing space), solid (inbox), ring
   (new space). Three SVGs shipped: mark, wordmark, 512x512 square
   for org/npm avatars.

2. Three-tier routing: comparison table at-a-glance + details
   blocks for drill-down. Cuts the section from three long bullet
   paragraphs into one table plus three foldable sections.

3. Quick start: the most-used flow (Chinese LLM) shows inline;
   OpenAI and zero-config variants fold into details blocks.

4. Entire English version wrapped in one details block. Chinese
   reader page length roughly halved. English reader clicks once.

5. GitHub Alerts added for the adapter tip and the project-status
   commitment, giving the page visual breathing points.

Plus a test count badge showing 249 passing.
